OL,3,CPC sacked for 'appalling' racist
OL,4,Cremark about colleague
OL,6,FThe force said the incident was
OL,7,Freported by a colleague, and referred
OL,8,Fit to the Independent Office for
OL,9,FPolice Conduct (IOPC), who carried out
OL,10,Fan investigation.
OL,12,FThe IOPC recommended that there were
OL,13,Fgrounds for gross misconduct, and at a
OL,14,Fhearing, Mr Dixon was dismissed and
OL,15,Fbarred from policing.
OL,17,FMr Dixon, 35, argued that the comment
OL,18,Fwas not used in a malicious manner and
OL,19,Fit was said while he was tired from
OL,20,Fsuccessive extended night shifts.
